Grammy hoopla. CBS's Grammy Awards telecast averaged 26.1 million viewers Sunday, a million more than last year to its best showing since 2014. 
'Dead' down. Against the Grammys, AMC's The Walking Dead returned with 12 million same-day viewers Sunday, down 23% from last February's start, while HBO's Girls began its sixth and final season with a typical 519,000. 
More winter openers. FX's Marvel series Legion premiered with a modest 1.6 million same-day viewers Wednesday. Fox's APB opened with 6.1 million Monday, holding onto its lead-in audience from 24: Legacy (6.2 million), which was down 65% from its post-Super Bowl return. Bravo drama Imposters premiered Tuesday with 655,000. <!--iframe--> Read or Share this story: http://usat.ly/2lgSt2c NEVER MISS OUT Life Be a pop culture maven.
